  "tune": "St. Anne",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Our God, our help in ages past, Our hope for years to come, Our shelter from the stormy blast, And our eternal home.",
    "v2": "Under the shadow of Thy throne Thy saints have dwelt secure; Sufficient is Thine arm alone, And our defense is sure.",
    "v3": "Before the hills in order stood, Or earth received her frame, From everlasting Thou art God, To endless years the same.",
    "v4": "Thy Word commands our flesh to dust, &#39;Return, ye sons of men:&#39; All nations rose from earth at first, And turn to earth again.",
    "v5": "A thousand ages in Thy sight Are like an evening gone; Short as the watch that ends the night Before the rising sun."
  },
